        <h2>Methodology: How We Rank The Assets</h2>
        <div style="line-height: 1.8;">
            <p>Our ranking of the top growth ETFs is based on a rigorous evaluation of quantitative performance metrics and qualitative fund characteristics. We analyze historical returns over 1-year, 3-year, and 5-year periods, assessing not just absolute performance but also risk-adjusted returns (such as the Sharpe ratio) to understand how much volatility investors endured to achieve those gains. Expense ratios are heavily weighted, as lower fees compound significantly over the long investment horizons typical of growth strategies.</p><p>Qualitatively, we dissect the fund's index construction methodology. We favor ETFs that utilize forward-looking growth metrics (like projected earnings growth) rather than solely relying on historical price momentum. We also evaluate the portfolio's concentration risk—assessing the percentage of assets held in the top 10 positions—and its sector diversification. Funds that provide robust exposure to sustainable growth themes while managing downside risks effectively are ranked highest in our analysis.</p>
        </div>
    </section>


